<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1166425139638">
<term>decimal</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1166424911849">A decimal is another way of writing a fraction whose denominator is a power of ten.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1166424911859">
<term>percent</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1166424911864">A percent is a ratio whose denominator is 100.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1166425061744">
<term>repeating decimal</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1166425061749">A repeating decimal is a decimal in which the last digit or group of digits repeats endlessly.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
